      <title>September 18th, 2017 Newsletter</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Almost one month ago, Anthem announced it would exit Virginia's Obamacare market entirely in 2018. While this is largely a federal issue, Virginia has been taking steps to try to find a solution to the problem created by Washington. We are hopeful that we may be able to work with an insurer to offer coverage in these localities without any providers, but that’s not a likely scenario. Unfortunately, the insurance providers are at the mercy of Washington’s inaction. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Mon, 18 Sep 2017 13:39:01 -0400</pubDate>
