      <title>September 11th, 2017 Newsletter</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The Trump Administration announced last Monday that it would end the Deferred Action Childhood Arrival (DACA) program established by executive order under President Barack Obama. The program will end in six months, giving Congress an opportunity to address the status of over 1.5 million people who came to America as undocumented children.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
